Parliamentary Debate Speech for the Deputy Minister of International Relations and Cooperation, Hon. Candith Mashego-Dlamini, for Parliamentary Debate on Russia – Ukraine Crisis, Tuesday, 15 March 2022 After the democratic elections in 1994, South Africa ceased to be the pariah of the world; it regained its rightful place in Africa, in the United Nations and in the family of nations. We emerged as a democratic country into a fundamentally transformed world. The development of South Africa’s post-apartheid foreign policy is guided by seven principles: South Africa’s approach on the Russia-Ukraine matter has been based on the following key principles, which in turn are based on our foreign policy: I THANK YOU NGIYABONGA Issued by Dirco, 15 March 2022